04:02.372 --> 04:03.504
Mm-hmm.

04:40.497 --> 04:43.413
Oh, passionfruit.
My favorite.

04:43.457 --> 04:45.415
Here, let me
pour you some coffee.

04:45.459 --> 04:47.112
Uh, no, thanks.

04:47.156 --> 04:48.113
I'm having tea this morning.

04:48.157 --> 04:49.332
What kind of tea?

04:49.376 --> 04:51.116
It's an herbal blend.

04:51.160 --> 04:52.857
Would you pass me
the salt, please?Sure.

04:52.901 --> 04:54.772
There you go.

04:55.947 --> 04:57.906
What's this for?

04:57.949 --> 04:59.081
You just asked for it.

04:59.124 --> 05:01.301
No, I asked for
sugar for my tea?

05:02.345 --> 05:04.434
Of course.

05:04.478 --> 05:06.480
My mistake.

05:08.046 --> 05:09.874
How do you feel?

05:09.918 --> 05:12.399
Mm, uh, great,
actually. Uh...

05:12.442 --> 05:15.010
You know, Blake buying
that pharma company

05:15.053 --> 05:16.664
might have been a
blessing in disguise.

05:16.707 --> 05:18.970
I don't see how that's possible.

05:19.014 --> 05:21.712
They were at least a decade awayfrom any sort of treatment.

05:21.756 --> 05:24.715
I don't have ten years to wait,
so what was I really chasing?

05:24.759 --> 05:27.283
Let Blake have it.And what are you gonna do?

05:27.327 --> 05:29.372
Well, I'm doing it.

05:29.416 --> 05:31.809
Nature's pharmacy.

05:31.853 --> 05:35.073
I've been reading up online, andmy acupuncturist hooked me up

05:35.117 --> 05:37.772
with this amazing doctor who
specializes in all this stuff.

05:37.815 --> 05:41.253
Hey, I am all forthe holistic approach,

05:41.297 --> 05:43.125
but Western medicine...

05:43.168 --> 05:44.735
I'm feeling good, Alexis.

05:44.779 --> 05:46.650
Better than I have
in a long time.

05:46.694 --> 05:48.826
I thought you'd
be happy for me.Of course.

05:48.870 --> 05:50.741
I... I am.

05:50.785 --> 05:53.396
